[While the behavior the animal in the beginning of the article may be
suspicious of rabies, it is unclear from this article if the animal
was ever tested for rabies. It is unclear if the missing and presumed
dead animal mentioned later is the same one.

Regular vaccination helps build a barrier between wildlife,
unvaccinated pets, and public health. Hopefully the vaccination
campaign started last year will either continue or be revived with
efforts to achieve a 100 per cent vaccination rate among domestic
pets. - Mod.TG

The interactive HealthMap/ProMED map for Tizayuca, Hidalgo, Mexico,
is available at http://healthmap.org/r/0Pxf - CopyEd.EJP]

